comments.body:
@rhatdan 
When I've discussed this fix with @jwhonce he told me to just create a draft PR to show where the problem lies. As far as I understood it, it is not going to be merged (please @jwhonce correct me if I'm wrong).
Once I get that information I can either close it, or resolve conflicts and merge it.

@msisj I have added functionality to API service in https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/13851 to read and parse the Path field to support this functionality.

Once that is reviewed and merged, updates for podman-py should be trivial. The format I went with is: `source`:`destination`:`permissions`

Fields after source are optional, with permissions copied from filesystem, destination copied from source.

@jwhonce can you re-review the changes. I've noticed that your mentioned PR to podman repository was declined as the options were possible to achieve with previous implementation.
So I've changed code a bit and implemented a test for devices options.
I've also changed the manifest test because it was failing but I'm not 100% sure what was changed on podman side and if the change is proper, just wanted to tests to pass, so please check it out too.
